The paper discusses the development of a new discipline within computer science focused on numerical algorithmic science and engineering. This is primarily related to numerical analysis and the algorithmic solution of numerical problems, which suggests that the most likely sub-category is cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). However, the paper also discusses the role of numerical analysts in the evolution of academic departments of computer science, which suggests that it may also be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science), cs.SE (Software Engineering), and cs.MS (Mathematical Software).
